  "texts": [
    "During the forward pass, for each linear layer in the network, the input x is stored in memory at every intermediate layer.",
    "This is necessary for backpropagation, as it is used to compute the gradient of the weights using the chain rule:",
    "Once the gradient is computed, it is used to update the weights in the subsequent time step",
    "Here, η represents the learning rate and ρ t is an element-wise operation defined by the choice of optimizer, such as Adam.",
    "Following the formulation in Zhao et al., 2024, GaLore projects the gradients into a lowerdimensional subspace before applying the optimizer, and projects them back to the original subspace for the weight update:"
  ],
